# 🎯 What is Async & Await?

---

## 🔹 async (Function)

### ✅ English:

`async` makes a function **always return a Promise**

### ✅ हिंदी:

`async` function हमेशा **Promise return करता है**

---

### Example:

```javascript
async function greet() {
    return "Hello";
}

greet().then(console.log);
```

👉 Output:

```javascript
Hello
```

👉 Behind the scenes:

```javascript
Promise.resolve("Hello");
```

---

# 🔹 await (Keyword)

### ✅ English:

`await` pauses execution until a Promise resolves

### ✅ हिंदी:

`await` Promise के पूरा होने तक code को रोक देता है (लेकिन पूरे program को block नहीं करता)

---

### Example:

```javascript
function delay() {
    return new Promise(resolve => {
        setTimeout(() => resolve("Done"), 2000);
    });
}

async function test() {
    console.log("Start");

    let result = await delay();

    console.log(result);
    console.log("End");
}

test();
```

---

### Output:

```
Start
(after 2 sec)
Done
End
```

---

# 🔥 Why use async/await?

| Problem          | Solution       |
| ---------------- | -------------- |
| Callback hell 😵 | Clean code     |
| .then chaining   | Easy reading   |
| Debugging hard   | Easy debugging |

---

# 🔥 Promise vs Async/Await

---

## Using Promise

```javascript
fetchData()
    .then(res => res.json())
    .then(data => console.log(data))
    .catch(err => console.log(err));
```

---

## Using async/await

```javascript
async function getData() {
    try {
        let res = await fetchData();
        let data = await res.json();
        console.log(data);
    } catch(err) {
        console.log(err);
    }
}
```

👉 हिंदी:
async/await readable और clean है

---

# 🔥 Real Example (API Call)

```javascript
async function getUsers() {
    let res = await fetch("https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users");
    let data = await res.json();
    console.log(data);
}

getUsers();
```

---

# 🔥 Error Handling (Important)

---

## Using try-catch

```javascript
async function test() {
    try {
        let res = await fetch("wrong-url");
        console.log(res);
    } catch (error) {
        console.log("Error:", error);
    }
}
```

👉 हिंदी:
error handle करने के लिए try-catch use करते हैं

---

# 🔥 Sequential vs Parallel Execution

---

## ❌ Sequential (Slow)

```javascript
let a = await task1();
let b = await task2();
```

---

## ✅ Parallel (Fast)

```javascript
let [a, b] = await Promise.all([task1(), task2()]);
```

👉 हिंदी:
Promise.all से speed बढ़ती है

---

# 🔥 Example: Parallel Execution

```javascript
async function run() {
    let results = await Promise.all([
        fetch("url1"),
        fetch("url2")
    ]);

    console.log(results);
}
```

---

# 🔥 await Rules ⚠️

---

## 1. Only inside async

```javascript
await fetch(); ❌
```

✔️ Correct:

```javascript
async function test() {
    await fetch();
}
```

---

## 2. Top-level await (Modern JS)

```javascript
let data = await fetch("url");
```

👉 Works in modules

---

# 🔥 Common Mistakes

---

## ❌ Forgetting await

```javascript
let data = fetch("url");
console.log(data); // Promise
```

---

## ✅ Correct

```javascript
let data = await fetch("url");
```

---

